cff-version: 1.2.0
message: >-
  If you use this software or the released trajectory archive, please cite
  the accompanying paper. The arXiv version (deanonymized) will replace
  this entry once posted.

title: "AgenticSTS: A Bounded-Memory Testbed for Long-Horizon LLM Agents"
abstract: >-
  AgenticSTS is a long-horizon LLM-agent testbed in Slay the Spire 2,
  built on a per-decision typed retrieval memory contract. The released
  archive contains 298 game trajectories with condition tags,
  SHA-anchored L4/L5 memory snapshots, prompt records, and reproducibility
  scripts. The accompanying paper reports a 3/10 to 6/10 win-rate lift at
  the lowest difficulty when triggered L5 skills are added under the
  contract, with layer-level ablation across three model backbones.
